OpenTelemetry Conventions

When implementing observability, follow OpenTelemetry best practices for metrics, logs, and traces. Consider the observability-expert skill for tracing, metrics, logging, exporters, and distributed systems visibility. Use /opentelemetry or @opentelemetry in Agent chat for full skill behavior.

Instrument services using OpenTelemetry SDK (auto-instrumentation when possible).

Propagate trace context across services (W3C Trace Context).

Avoid logging sensitive data (PII/PHI).

Use structured logging (JSON format preferred).

Correlate logs with trace IDs.

Expose metrics in Prometheus-compatible format.

Define SLO-based metrics (latency, error rate, throughput).

Avoid high-cardinality labels in metrics.

Ensure trace sampling strategy is environment-aware.
